abstract: Fast, frugal and robust, rules of thumb are decision-making powerhouses.
snippet: Fast, frugal and robust, rules of thumb are decision-making powerhouses.
lead_paragraph: The economist-approved way to make hard choices is to maximize your expected utility (pleasure, benefit), which involves a complex weighing of the pros and cons of each option, including the likelihood of each one actually happening. That can be a tough slog, though, even if all youre trying to do is choose between the meat lovers omelet and the spanakopita.

main: In Praise of the Humble Rule of Thumb

abstract: The international team prepared to cross the front lines to inspect the embattled, Russian-held Zaporizhzhia plant, but it was not clear how long the Russians would let them stay.
snippet: The international team prepared to cross the front lines to inspect the embattled, Russian-held Zaporizhzhia plant, but it was not clear how long the Russians would let them stay.
lead_paragraph: ZAPORIZHZHIA, Ukraine  An international team of nuclear experts on Wednesday approached the combat zone in Russias war on Ukraine, preparing to cross over the front lines on Thursday to inspect the imperiled, Russian-occupied Zaporizhzhia Nuclear Power Plant, in one of the most complex and perilous missions of its kind ever attempted.

main: U.N. Experts Plan Perilous Visit to Ukrainian Nuclear Plant Thursday
print_headline: U.N. Inspectors Plan Perilous Visit to Nuclear Power Plant in Battle Zone

lead_paragraph: They rushed to Ukraine by the thousands, many of them Americans who promised to bring military experience, money or supplies to the battleground of a righteous war. Hometown newspapers hailed their commitment, and donors backed them with millions of dollars.

abstract: Alice Elliott Darks ambitious new novel, Fellowship Point, explores a lifetime of lessons about friendship, loyalty and land.
snippet: Alice Elliott Darks ambitious new novel, Fellowship Point, explores a lifetime of lessons about friendship, loyalty and land.
lead_paragraph: Novels featuring older characters are well suited to an exploration of questions about time, history and change. Unlike younger protagonists, they already know who theyve become and what theyve made of their lives. Theyre not finished yet, but they are as busy reckoning with the past as they are living in the present. They are in full possession of the bulk of their lifes trajectory, so their primary aim is to resolve and make sense of things before they die.

main: Pay Attention to These Old Women. Youll Learn Something.

snippet: Prosecutors had recommended three years in prison for Diana Toebbe, but a federal judge sentenced her to almost 22 years, a longer term than her husband.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON  A federal judge sentenced a Navy engineer to 19 years in prison on Wednesday and  in an unusual twist  handed his wife nearly 22 years for the couples botched attempt to sell sensitive nuclear propulsion secrets to a foreign country.

main: Judge Gives Long Sentence to Couple Who Tried to Sell Submarine Secrets
print_headline: Long Prison Terms for Couple Who Tried To Sell Secrets About Nuclear Submarines

abstract: A primer on the filmmakers career and interests wont offer much that will surprise even mild obsessives, but it does pierce some of the mystique.
snippet: A primer on the filmmakers career and interests wont offer much that will surprise even mild obsessives, but it does pierce some of the mystique.
lead_paragraph: The director Stanley Kubrick gave so few interviews that hearing his voice is always a little jarring. Its less deep than you might imagine from late-career photographs, which make him look like a woolly elder statesman of the cinema, or from seeing his movies, which raise dark questions about human nature. Kubricks accent contains traces of his Bronx upbringing, even though he lived in Britain for more than 30 years. And his conversational manner is much more casual, more affable, than his reputation as a hermetic perfectionist would suggest.

main: Kubrick by Kubrick Review: Stanley Plays Himself
print_headline: A Master Director in Front of the Camera

main: A U.S. Ambassador Finds Himself on Hostile Ground in Hungary
